  "doc_id": "8656",
  "text": "In this paper we have shown that many important learning and inference problems can be solved efficiently for non-projective edge-factored dependency models by appealing to the Matrix Tree Theorem for multi-digraphs. These results extend the work of [CITATION_1] and help to further our understanding of when exact non-projective algorithms can be employed. When this analysis is coupled with the projective parsing algorithms of [CITATION_2] and [CITATION_3] we begin to get a clear picture of the complexity for data-driven dependency parsing within an edge-factored framework. To further justify the algorithms presented here, we outlined a few novel learning and inference settings in which they are required.",
